<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/Regressive" class="external text" title="http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/Regressive" rel="nofollow">Webster</a> (3): decreasing in rate as the base increases (a regressive tax)</li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.bartleby.com/61/71/R0127100.html" class="external text" title="http://www.bartleby.com/61/71/R0127100.html" rel="nofollow">American Heritage</a> (3). Decreasing proportionately as the amount taxed increases: a regressive tax.</li>
