<li id="cite_note-greenspan-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-greenspan_30-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFAndrews2005">Andrews, Edmund L. (2005-03-04). <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2005/03/04/politics/04tax.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2005/03/04/politics/04tax.html" rel="nofollow">"Fed's Chief Gives Consumption Tax Cautious Backing"</a> (HTML). <a href="/wiki/The_New_York_Times" title="The New York Times">The New York Times</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2005/03/04/politics/04tax.html" class="external free" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2005/03/04/politics/04tax.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.nytimes.com/2005/03/04/politics/04tax.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-02-05</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Fed%27s+Chief+Gives+Consumption+Tax+Cautious+Backing&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Andrews&amp;rft.aufirst=Edmund+L.&amp;rft.au=Andrews%2C+Edmund+L.&amp;rft.date=2005-03-04&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BThe+New+York+Times%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2005%2F03%2F04%2Fpolitics%2F04tax.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Progressive_tax"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
